The paper focuses on human detection and tracking using a mobile robot, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of multiple sensors, including RGB-D cameras and 2D LiDAR, for learning a 3D LiDAR-based human classifier suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) are also relevant sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of trajectory probability and semi-supervised learning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
